<task id="WKSP-030" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build dynamic workspace config builder function</title>
    <phase>4</phase>
    <tags>shared-components, frontend</tags>
    <estimated-effort>6h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>001, 002, 016</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Create the buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig() function that merges stored layout JSON with the SECTION_REGISTRY to produce a WorkspaceConfig consumable by WorkspaceShell.</goal>
    <context>
      The workspace personalization feature stores user layouts as JSON in the sprk_sectionsjson column of
      sprk_workspacelayout records. Each layout JSON contains a schemaVersion, a grid template definition,
      and an array of slot assignments mapping section IDs to grid positions.

      The SECTION_REGISTRY (created in Task 002) maps section IDs to SectionRegistration objects with factory
      functions. The dynamic config builder must reconcile these two data sources: the layout JSON says
      "which sections go where" and the registry says "how to create each section."

      This function replaces the hardcoded buildWorkspaceConfig() currently in workspaceConfig.tsx. It must
      handle edge cases gracefully: unknown section IDs (removed/renamed), more sections than slots,
      empty rows, and schema version mismatches.

      A SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT constant provides the fallback layout matching the current hardcoded config.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Function MUST live in LegalWorkspace src (not shared library) since it depends on SECTION_REGISTRY
      - MUST validate schemaVersion field and reject unsupported versions with console.warn + fallback
      - MUST skip sections whose IDs are not found in SECTION_REGISTRY with console.warn (not throw)
      - MUST handle slot overflow: if more sections than template slots, auto-append 1fr rows to grid
      - MUST skip empty rows (rows where no sections were assigned after filtering)
      - MUST export a SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT constant matching the current hardcoded 5-section config
      - MUST accept SectionFactoryContext as a parameter and pass it to each section factory
      - Return type MUST be WorkspaceConfig (from @spaarke/ui-components)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/types.ts</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/workspaceConfig.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/types.ts</file>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read the existing workspaceConfig.tsx and WorkspaceShell types.ts to understand the current WorkspaceConfig shape and how sections are wired today.</step>
    <step id="2">Define the LayoutJson TypeScript interface representing the stored layout structure: schemaVersion, gridTemplate (rows/columns), and slots array with sectionId and grid position properties.</step>
    <step id="3">Create the SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT constant that mirrors the current hardcoded 5-section layout, using the same section IDs from SECTION_REGISTRY.</step>
    <step id="4">Implement buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig(layoutJson, registry, context) with schemaVersion validation — if version is unsupported, console.warn and fall back to SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT.</step>
    <step id="5">Add section resolution logic: iterate slots, look up each sectionId in registry, call factory(context) for found sections, console.warn and skip missing IDs.</step>
    <step id="6">Add slot overflow handling: if resolved sections exceed template slot count, compute additional 1fr rows and extend the grid template accordingly.</step>
    <step id="7">Add empty row filtering: after section assignment, remove any grid rows that contain no sections.</step>
    <step id="8">Verify TypeScript compilation and ensure the function signature returns WorkspaceConfig compatible with WorkspaceShell props.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig() accepts layout JSON, SECTION_REGISTRY, and SectionFactoryContext and returns a valid WorkspaceConfig</criterion>
    <criterion>Unknown section IDs are skipped with console.warn, not thrown as errors</criterion>
    <criterion>Slot overflow auto-appends 1fr rows to accommodate extra sections</criterion>
    <criterion>Empty rows (no assigned sections after filtering) are removed from the final grid</criterion>
    <criterion>SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT constant is exported and matches the current 5-section hardcoded layout</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
